WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.767
[Speaker, describing a graph on screen]: As you can see, the employment rate for Americans without disabilities is much higher than those with disabilities

2
00:00:07.767 --> 00:00:13.563
[Speaker]: In general,  we have seen people with disabilities employed at nearly half the rate of those without disabilities

3
00:00:13.563 --> 00:00:20.620
The onscreen graph  shows that in 1991, employment was 50.2 percent for disabled people and 84.4 percent for non-disabled. In 2010, the numbers were 41.1 and 79.1 respectively

